BASIC EXAMPLE - HORIZONTAL LAYOUT

  • more_vert
    • Action
    • Another action
    • Something else here

First Step

Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Integer ut nulla nunc. Maecenas arcu sem, hendrerit a tempor quis, sagittis accumsan tellus. In hac habitasse platea dictumst. Donec a semper dui. Nunc eget quam libero. Nam at felis metus. Nam tellus dolor, tristique ac tempus nec, iaculis quis nisi.

Second Step

Donec mi sapien, hendrerit nec egestas a, rutrum vitae dolor. Nullam venenatis diam ac ligula elementum pellentesque. In lobortis sollicitudin felis non eleifend. Morbi tristique tellus est, sed tempor elit. Morbi varius, nulla quis condimentum dictum, nisi elit condimentum magna, nec venenatis urna quam in nisi. Integer hendrerit sapien a diam adipiscing consectetur. In euismod augue ullamcorper leo dignissim quis elementum arcu porta. Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Vestibulum leo velit, blandit ac tempor nec, ultrices id diam. Donec metus lacus, rhoncus sagittis iaculis nec, malesuada a diam. Donec non pulvinar urna. Aliquam id velit lacus.

Third Step

Morbi ornare tellus at elit ultrices id dignissim lorem elementum. Sed eget nisl at justo condimentum dapibus. Fusce eros justo, pellentesque non euismod ac, rutrum sed quam. Ut non mi tortor. Vestibulum eleifend varius ullamcorper. Aliquam erat volutpat. Donec diam massa, porta vel dictum sit amet, iaculis ac massa. Sed elementum dui commodo lectus sollicitudin in auctor mauris venenatis.

Forth Step

Quisque at sem turpis, id sagittis diam. Suspendisse malesuada eros posuere mauris vehicula vulputate. Aliquam sed sem tortor. Quisque sed felis ut mauris feugiat iaculis nec ac lectus. Sed consequat vestibulum purus, imperdiet varius est pellentesque vitae. Suspendisse consequat cursus eros, vitae tempus enim euismod non. Nullam ut commodo tortor.

RANGE SLIDERS

EXAMPLES Taken by Ion Range Slider which link is ionden.com/a/plugins/ion.rangeSlider/en.html

  • more_vert
    • Action
    • Another action
    • Something else here
Start without params
Set min value, max value and start point
Set type to double and specify range, also showing grid and adding prefix "$"
Set up range with negative values
Using step 250
Set up range with fractional values, using fractional step
Set up you own numbers
Using any strings as your values
One more example with strings
No prettify. Big numbers are ugly and unreadable

PAGINATION

DEFAULT PAGINATION Simple pagination inspired by Rdio, great for apps and search results. The large block is hard to miss, easily scalable, and provides large click areas.

  • more_vert

    • Another action

LIST GROUPS

BASIC EXAMPLES The most basic list group is simply an unordered list with list items, and the proper classes.

  • more_vert
    • Action
    • Another action
    • Something else here
  • Cras justo odio
  • Dapibus ac facilisis in
  • Morbi leo risus
  • Porta ac consectetur ac
  • Vestibulum at eros

BADGES Add the badges component to any list group item and it will automatically be positioned on the right.

  • more_vert
    • Action
    • Another action
    • Something else here
  • Cras justo odio 14 new
  • Dapibus ac facilisis in 99 read
  • Morbi leo risus 99+
  • Porta ac consectetur ac 21
  • Vestibulum at eros 18

LINKED ITEMS Linkify list group items by using anchor tags instead of list items (that also means a parent <div> instead of an <ul>). No need for individual parents around each element.

  • more_vert
    • Action
    • Another action
    • Something else here
Cras justo odio Dapibus ac facilisis in Morbi leo risus Porta ac consectetur ac Vestibulum at eros

BUTTON ITEMS List group items may be buttons instead of list items (that also means a parent <div> instead of an <ul>). No need for individual parents around each element. Don't use the standard .btn classes here.

  • more_vert
    • Action
    • Another action
    • Something else here

DISABLED ITEMS Add .disabled to a .list-group-item to gray it out to appear disabled.

  • more_vert
    • Action
    • Another action
    • Something else here
Cras justo odio Dapibus ac facilisis in Morbi leo risus Porta ac consectetur ac Vestibulum at eros

COLLAPSE

EXAMPLE Click the buttons below to show and hide another element via class changes. You can use a link with the href attribute, or a button with the data-target attribute. In both cases, the data-toggle="collapse" is required.

  • more_vert

    • Another action

MARGIN & PADDING SPACES You can use classes which names are .m-t-10, .m-t--10, .m-r-5, .p-t-10, .p-b-5

  • more_vert
    • Action
    • Another action
    • Something else here

Margins

Margin Top 10px → .m-t-10
Margin Top 0px → .m-t-0
Margin Top -10px → .m-t--10
Margin Left 35px → .m-l-35
Margin Left 0px → .m-l-0
Margin Left -35px → .m-l--35
Margin Bottom 15px → .m-b-15
Margin Bottom 0px → .m-b-0
Margin Bottom -20px → .m-b--20
Margin Right 30px → .m-r-30
Margin Right 0px → .m-r-0
Margin Right -30px → .m-r--30
ALL Margin 0px → .margin-0

Paddings

Padding Top 10px → .p-t-10
Padding Top 0px → .p-t-0
Padding Left 35px → .p-l-35
Padding Left 0px → .p-l-0
Padding Bottom 15px → .p-b-15
Padding Bottom 0px → .p-b-0
Padding Right 30px → .p-r-30
Padding Right 0px → .p-r-0
ALL Padding 0px → .padding-0

SPECIAL CLASSES FOR EVERY BROWSERS When the user start the usage this theme, we put the browser info inside the html as class

  • more_vert
    • Action
    • Another action
    • Something else here
Putting classes are .ie10, .ie11, .edge, .opera, .chrome, .firefox, .safari to class inside of html element. So you can create new classes for run only you specified browser(s).

Example

/* It will be work only IE10 */
html.ie10 .menu .list {
   background-color: #CC0000;
}
/* It will be work only Google Chrome */
html.chrome .right-sidebar .header {
   font-size: 15px;
   font-weight: bold;
}
